'''Water Efficiency Labelling and Standard (WELS)''' is a labeling scheme initiated by the [[Australian Government]] to help Australian households [[water conservation|conserve water]] and money. On 1 July 2006, it became mandatory across [[Australia]] to carry a (WELS) Water Rating label when selling showers, [[washing machine]]s, [[dishwasher]]s, toilet equipment, [[urinal]] equipment and [[tap (valve)|tap]] equipment intended for use over kitchen [[sink]]s, [[bathroom]] basins, [[laundry]] tubs or ablution troughs.

