'''Yorkshire and Humber Assembly''' was the [[regional chamber]] for the [[Yorkshire and the Humber]] region of [[England]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yhassembly.gov.uk/ |title=Yorkshire & Humber Assembly|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080501072529/http://www.yhassembly.gov.uk/ |archivedate=1 May 2008 |accessdate=17 March 2008}}</ref> It closed on 31 March 2009.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/features/The-short-life-and-changing.5124376.jp|title=The short life and changing times of a people's parliament that never was|work=Yorkshire Post|accessdate=1 April 2009}}</ref> The responsibilities of the assembly were assumed by a [[Yorkshire and Humber Joint Regional Board|Joint Regional Board]] consisting of members of [[Yorkshire Forward]], the [[Regional Development Agency]], and [[Local Government Yorkshire and Humber]], a regional partnership of local authorities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lgyh.gov.uk/News/New-Regional-Arrangements/ |title=New Regional Arrangements|publisher=Local Government Yorkshire and Humber|accessdate=11 April 2009}}</ref>

